Uses of Package
com.cyc.kb.client

  • Packages that use com.cyc.kb.client 
    Package Description
    com.cyc.kb.client
    The implementation of various interfaces specified in com.cyc.kb, refer to that package for a more detailed discussion of using the API.
    com.cyc.kb.config
    This package contains useful configuration utilities of the KB API.
    com.cyc.kb.quant
    Provides quantifications, not fully supported in current release, and subject to change.
  • Classes in com.cyc.kb.client used by com.cyc.kb.client 
    Class and Description
    AssertionImpl
    An Assertion object is a facade for a #$CycLAssertion in Cyc KB.
    BinaryPredicateImpl
    A BinaryPredicate object is a facade for a #$BinaryPredicate in Cyc KB.
    Constants
    A convenience class for frequently accessed Cyc constants.
    ContextImpl
    A Context object is a facade for a #$Microtheory in Cyc KB.
    FactImpl
    A fact object is an assertion with a variable-free sentence with no conjunctions or operators (a ground atomic formula), and a facade for #$CycLGAFAssertion.
    FirstOrderCollectionImpl
    A FirstOrderCollection object is a facade for a #$FirstOrderCollection in Cyc KB.
    KBCollectionImpl
    A KBCollection object is a facade for a #$Collection in Cyc KB.
    KBFunctionImpl
    A KBFunction object is a facade for a #$Function-Denotational in the Cyc KB.
    KBIndividualImpl
    A KBIndividual object is a facade for a #$Individual in Cyc KB.
    KBObjectImpl
    The base class for all the other classes in this package.
    KBObjectImpl.KBURIType 
    KBPredicateImpl
    A KBPredicate object is a facade for a #$Predicate in Cyc KB.
    KBTermImpl
    A KBTerm is a facade for any #$CycLDenotationalTerm, but in the API its purpose is to create terms that are only known to be #$Thing.
